832 A.2d 833 ATTORNEY GRIEVANCE COMMISSION OF MARYLAND, Petitioner. v. Antoine I. MANN, Respondent. Misc. AG No. 9,

Sept. Term, 2003.

Court of Appeals of Maryland. Sept. 23, 2003.

ORDER

Upon consideration of the Joint Petition for Indefinite Suspension by Consent filed herein, pursuant to Maryland Rule 16-772, it is this 23rd day of September, 2003.

ORDERED, by the Court of Appeals of Maryland, that Antoine Ian Mann be and is hereby indefinitely suspended by consent from the further practice of law in the State of Maryland, effective immediately, and it is further,

ORDERED, that Judgment shall be entered in favor of Petitioner, the Attorney Grievance Commission of Maryland, in the amount of $6,474.85 for costs against Antoine Ian Mann, and it is further,

ORDERED, that the Clerk of this Court shall strike the name of Antoine Ian Mann from the register of attorneys, and pursuant to Maryland Rule 16-772(d), shall certify that fact to the Trustees of the Client Protection Fund and the Clerks of all judicial tribunals in the State.
